abstract: The Tennessee Republican was a protege of Senator Howard H. Baker Jr., another Republican from Tennessee, who turned against Richard Nixon. Now Mr. Alexander may hold the fate of President Trump in his hands.
snippet: The Tennessee Republican was a protege of Senator Howard H. Baker Jr., another Republican from Tennessee, who turned against Richard Nixon. Now Mr. Alexander may hold the fate of President Trump in his hands.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The ghost of Howard H. Baker Jr., the Republican senator from Tennessee who turned against Richard M. Nixon during Watergate, is hovering over Senator Lamar Alexander.

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lashed out in anger Saturday at an NPR reporter who accused him of shouting expletives at her after she asked him in an interview about Ukraine. In a direct and personal attack, America's chief diplomat said the journalist had “lied” to him and he called her conduct “shameful.”
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lashed out in anger Saturday at an NPR reporter who accused him of shouting expletives at her after she asked him in an interview about Ukraine. In a direct and personal attack, America's chief diplomat said the jour...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lashed out in anger Saturday at an NPR reporter who accused him of shouting expletives at her after she asked him in an interview about Ukraine. In a direct and personal attack, America's chief diplomat said the journalist had “lied” to him and he called her conduct “shameful.”
headline_main: Pompeo Lashes Out at Journalist; NPR Defends Its Reporter
headline_print_headline: Pompeo Lashes Out at Journalist; NPR Defends Its Reporter

abstract: President Trump’s lawyers sought to provide alternative explanations for his actions toward Ukraine.
snippet: President Trump’s lawyers sought to provide alternative explanations for his actions toward Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers wrapped up a brief opening argument against his impeachment on Saturday much as they had begun, seeking to turn accusations of wrongdoing back on Democrats and insisting that there were innocent explanations for Mr. Trump’s actions toward Ukraine.
headline_main: Trump’s defense team seeks to sow reasonable doubt.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump’s special envoy for Serbia and Kosovo said Saturday that an agreement to resume railway service between the two Balkan rivals is important for both nations.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump’s special envoy for Serbia and Kosovo said Saturday that an agreement to resume railway service between the two Balkan rivals is important for both nations.
lead_paragraph: BELGRADE, Serbia — U.S. President Donald Trump’s special envoy for Serbia and Kosovo said Saturday that an agreement to resume railway service between the two Balkan rivals is important for both nations.
headline_main: Trump Envoy Hails Deal to Resume Serbia-Kosovo Rail Service
headline_print_headline: Trump Envoy Hails Deal to Resume Serbia-Kosovo Rail Service

abstract: After a three-day presentation from House Democrats, President Trump’s lawyers took the stage in a short Saturday session to begin arguing against his removal. Here were the highlights.
snippet: After a three-day presentation from House Democrats, President Trump’s lawyers took the stage in a short Saturday session to begin arguing against his removal. Here were the highlights.
lead_paragraph: After three days of arguments by the House managers prosecuting President Trump for high crimes and misdemeanors, the president’s lawyers presented the senators a radically different view of the facts and the Constitution, seeking to turn the Democrats’ charges back on them while denouncing the whole process as illegitimate.

abstract: Mr. Pompeo issued a statement to denounce a reporter who said on the air this week that he had privately lashed out at her with profanities
snippet: Mr. Pompeo issued a statement to denounce a reporter who said on the air this week that he had privately lashed out at her with profanities
lead_paragraph: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo, who has tried to distance himself from what he calls “the noise” of the impeachment proceedings, issued an extraordinary official statement Saturday accusing a veteran NPR reporter who pressed him about his role in the Ukraine affair had “lied” to him and was a “shameful” example of the “unhinged” anti-Trump news media.
headline_main: Pompeo accuses a reporter of lying.

abstract: More than two years after he first proposed a peace plan for Israel and the Palestinians, U.S. President Donald Trump said on Thursday he would reveal details on how he will tackle the long intractable political issues within days.
snippet: More than two years after he first proposed a peace plan for Israel and the Palestinians, U.S. President Donald Trump said on Thursday he would reveal details on how he will tackle the long intractable political issues within days.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — More than two years after he first proposed a peace plan for Israel and the Palestinians, U.S. President Donald Trump said on Thursday he would reveal details on how he will tackle the long intractable political issues within days.
headline_main: Explainer: What Do We Know About Trump's Mideast Peace Plan?

abstract: Patrick Philbin, who argued on the president’s behalf on Saturday, was a close ally of James B. Comey.
snippet: Patrick Philbin, who argued on the president’s behalf on Saturday, was a close ally of James B. Comey.
lead_paragraph: Patrick Philbin, one of the White House lawyers who argued on behalf of President Trump on the Senate floor on Saturday, once worked for James B. Comey, not exactly a favorite of his current boss.

headline_main: Trump impeachment lawyer once worked for his nemesis, Comey.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates roared back into Iowa on Saturday touting fresh endorsements, critiquing their rivals and predicting victories in the caucuses that will soon launch the process of deciding who will challenge President Donald Trump.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates roared back into Iowa on Saturday touting fresh endorsements, critiquing their rivals and predicting victories in the caucuses that will soon launch the process of deciding who will challenge President Donald Tru...
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidates roared back into Iowa on Saturday touting fresh endorsements, critiquing their rivals and predicting victories in the caucuses that will soon launch the process of deciding who will challenge President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Volatility Defines Democratic Race as Candidates Flood Iowa
headline_print_headline: Volatility Defines Democratic Race as Candidates Flood Iowa

abstract: Patrick Philbin was a senior official in the Justice Department under President George W. Bush.
snippet: Patrick Philbin was a senior official in the Justice Department under President George W. Bush.
lead_paragraph: Patrick Philbin, the White House lawyer arguing on behalf of President Trump on the Senate floor on Saturday, once worked for James B. Comey, not exactly a favorite of his current boss.
headline_main: One Trump lawyer once worked for Comey.
